1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,950
First order logic is an expansion of propositional logic, where we

2
00:00:04,050 --> 00:00:07,632
add variables and quantifiers to our set of logical symbols.

3
00:00:09,666 --> 00:00:13,068
We also add certain constant, function and relation

4
00:00:13,168 --> 00:00:16,227
symbols, which are specific to a given theory.

5
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:20,383
For example, if we want to study the natural numbers, we add the

6
00:00:20,483 --> 00:00:24,599
constant 0, the successor function S, which just maps n to n plus

7
00:00:24,699 --> 00:00:29,268
1, the addition and multiplication function, and the less than relation.

8
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:32,753
But if we want to study graphs, all we would need

9
00:00:32,853 --> 00:00:37,279
is a single binary relation E expressing an edge between nodes.

10
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:39,825
These symbols which are specific to a

11
00:00:39,925 --> 00:00:43,189
given theory are called the non-logical symbols,

12
00:00:43,266 --> 00:00:46,014
and these are the logical symbols.

13
00:00:46,066 --> 00:00:49,231
If we restrict ourselves to the logical symbols, then

14
00:00:49,331 --> 00:00:51,633
we are in the domain of pure logic, and

15
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:55,083
whatever we prove applies to all first order structures.

16
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:57,623
The syntax of first order logic is

17
00:00:57,723 --> 00:01:00,519
given by the so-called logical axioms.

18
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:03,003
We note that we have just added three

19
00:01:03,103 --> 00:01:06,116
axioms to the axioms of propositional logic...

20
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:11,107
which determine how the forall quantifiers work. Note that since exists x P

21
00:01:11,207 --> 00:01:15,847
x, where P is some arbitrary property like being even, is equivalent to

22
00:01:15,947 --> 00:01:19,453
not forall x not P x. If there is an even number, then

23
00:01:19,553 --> 00:01:23,125
we know that not all numbers are odd, so this is why we

24
00:01:23,225 --> 00:01:27,598
technically only need to add the forall quantifier to the language.

25
00:01:27,666 --> 00:01:30,930
One can show that this set of axioms is once again

26
00:01:31,030 --> 00:01:34,966
sound and complete, but this time for first order logic, and

27
00:01:35,066 --> 00:01:37,858
we will see this proof in the fourth video.

28
00:01:37,933 --> 00:01:41,794
Often the equality relation is taken to be a logical symbol. In

29
00:01:41,894 --> 00:01:45,442
this case, we need to add the following five axioms to our

30
00:01:45,542 --> 00:01:50,032
list of logical axioms which define the behaviour of the equality symbol.

31
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:55,444
These axioms are hard to argue against, everything is equal to itself, if a

32
00:01:55,544 --> 00:01:59,123
is equal to b then b is also equal to a, and so on.

33
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:03,187
Now we are ready to move to the semantics of

34
00:02:03,287 --> 00:02:06,836
FOL. Again we fix our language, which again means we

35
00:02:06,936 --> 00:02:10,836
pick a set of constant, function and relations symbols...

36
00:02:10,933 --> 00:02:13,497
and we can define a structure,

37
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:16,304
which is represented by this fancy M, and

38
00:02:16,404 --> 00:02:18,698
is equal to this tuple of elements.

39
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:21,886
This is the domain or universe of the structure...

40
00:02:22,466 --> 00:02:26,415
and these are the 'interpretations' of the symbols in the language.

41
00:02:26,466 --> 00:02:30,546
Constants are interpreted as specific elements in the structure...

42
00:02:30,666 --> 00:02:34,018
and functions and relations are interpreted as subsets

43
00:02:34,118 --> 00:02:36,574
of tuples of elements of the structures.

44
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:41,286
This is a bit abstract, so lets consider the example of the

45
00:02:41,386 --> 00:02:45,283
standard structure of arithmetic, which is essentially just a number line.

46
00:02:45,333 --> 00:02:48,080
Again we work within the language of arithmetic.

47
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:52,134
So, the universe is the set of natural numbers.

48
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:55,260
We can visualize this structure as a the number line,

49
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:58,242
and as we would expect, the interpretation of 0 is

50
00:02:58,342 --> 00:03:00,746
just the first element in the number line.

51
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:06,189
The interpretations of the relations and functions are harder to visualize. But

52
00:03:06,289 --> 00:03:10,358
formally we interpret the less than symbol as the set of all

53
00:03:10,458 --> 00:03:14,388
pairs of natural numbers (x,y) such that x is less than y.

54
00:03:14,533 --> 00:03:17,929
The successor function will map to the set of all pairs of

55
00:03:18,029 --> 00:03:21,486
numbers such that the second is one greater than the first.

56
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:25,959
Similarly for the addition function, it maps to the set of

57
00:03:26,059 --> 00:03:29,650
all triples (x,y,z) such that x plus y equals z.

58
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:33,739
So in general the interpretation function s is the bridge between

59
00:03:33,839 --> 00:03:37,593
syntax and semantics, where s is a function which maps symbols

60
00:03:37,693 --> 00:03:41,446
in a formal language, either to elements, or subsets of tuples

61
00:03:41,546 --> 00:03:44,119
of elements of the domain of the structure.

62
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:49,674
This is a strange and abstract idea, to get a better understanding,

63
00:03:49,774 --> 00:03:54,112
let us move to perhaps the simplest theory, the theory of graphs.

64
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:59,220
The language has a single binary relation E, and models are arbitrary sets

65
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:03,164
of points, which may or may not be connected by an arrow.

66
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:07,214
Where given nodes a and b, a E b if and

67
00:04:07,314 --> 00:04:11,224
only if there is an arrow from a to b.

